---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — Autonomy Bridge"
  description="Autonomy Bridge provides warehouse automation economic analysis for operators, investors, and vendors making high-stakes robotics and AMR deployment decisions."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="container site-main">
    <h1>About Autonomy Bridge</h1>

    <section class="section reading-column">
      <p class="subhead">
        Autonomy Bridge specializes in AI and robotics market research, industrial automation GTM
        analysis, and enterprise AI commercialization research.
      </p>
      <p>
        The firm focuses on the economic boundary between technical capability and market viability.
      </p>
      <p>
        Autonomy Bridge operates independently and does not perform implementation or integration work.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section reading-column section-alt">
      <h2>Primary Domain</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>AI</li>
        <li>Robotics</li>
        <li>Industrial automation</li>
        <li>Physical AI systems</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section reading-column">
      <h2>Secondary Domain</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Enterprise SaaS</li>
        <li>Platform infrastructure</li>
        <li>Regulated workflows</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section reading-column section-alt">
      <h2>The Autonomy Bridge Commercialization Framework</h2>
      <p>Every engagement follows a four-stage logic to move from uncertainty to decision.</p>
      <div class="framework">
        <div class="stage">
          <h3>Stage 1: Market Reality Check</h3>
          <p>Is there a buyer with budget, urgency, and authority?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <h3>Stage 2: Adoption Feasibility</h3>
          <p>What blocks deployment, scale, or internal approval?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <h3>Stage 3: Economic Viability</h3>
          <p>Do pricing and unit economics work under real constraints?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stage">
          <h3>Stage 4: Go / No-Go Decision</h3>
          <p>Proceed, pause, or stop — with explicit trade-offs stated.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section reading-column">
      <h2>Methodology</h2>
      <p>
        Every engagement applies a utilization-first economic model that evaluates whether
        a warehouse can sustain the utilization required to recover automation capital — before
        assessing technology fit, vendor selection, or implementation scope.
      </p>
      <p>
        Analysis covers the full workflow chain: receiving, storage, replenishment, picking,
        transport, packing, sortation, and outbound staging. Recommendations are structured
        as decision briefs with explicit conditions, risk factors, and confidence bounds.
      </p>
      <p>
        Autonomy Bridge does not perform implementation or integration work, and does not
        accept commercial arrangements with automation vendors being evaluated.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/methodology">Read the full methodology →</a></p>
    </section>

    <section class="section reading-column">
      <h2>Principal</h2>
      <p>
        Autonomy Bridge is led by Deepak Gupta, who has supported commercialization, pricing,
        and market-entry decisions across AI, robotics, industrial automation, and enterprise
        B2B SaaS.
      </p>
      <p>
        Work has included pricing and RaaS model decisions for autonomous systems, market entry
        analysis across North America, Europe, and Asia, and commercialization planning for
        enterprise AI and automation platforms.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/deepakgupta5" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          LinkedIn →
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section reading-column">
      <h2>Work With Us</h2>
      <p>
        Engagements begin with a structured conversation about the decision you are facing
        and whether independent analysis would change the outcome.
      </p>
      <p class="inline-actions">
        <a href="/advisory" class="btn-primary">Advisory Services</a>
        <a href="/contact">Start a Conversation →</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
